[[["nmod:tmod", "nsubj", "nummod", "advmod", "compound", "aux", "dobj", "nmod", "case", "nmod:poss", "amod", "cc", "conj"], "Today, about 4 billion people are using English for their everyday life and work."], [["nmod", "case", "det", "compound", "nsubj", "nummod", "advmod", "cop", "ccomp", "nsubj", "amod", "cc", "conj", "nummod", "cop", "amod"], "Of this 4 billion, about 40 % are native English speakers and 60% are non-native speakers."], [["advcl", "mark", "nsubj", "xcomp", "det", "amod", "amod", "nmod", "case", "det", "nsubj", "aux", "nmod", "case", "det", "amod", "nmod", "case"], "As English becomes an important second language throughout the world, it is changing into a simpler version of itself."], [["nmod", "case", "det", "amod", "nsubj", "compound", "aux", "dep", "advmod", "nmod", "case", "nmod:poss", "det", "case"], "During the last century, American English was getting more popular than the Queen's English."], [["advmod", "nsubj", "det", "amod", "aux", "nmod", "case", "det", "amod", "amod"], "Now, the English language is transforming into a new global language."], [["nsubj", "xcomp", "nsubj", "amod", "cc", "conj", "amod", "nmod", "case"], "People call it global English or Globish-a tool of communication."], [["nsubj", "xcomp", "mark", "dobj", "nmod", "case", "amod", "advcl", "mark", "advmod"], "Globish aims to help people from different countries to communicate easily."], [["nmod", "case", "det", "expl", "nsubj", "det", "nmod", "case", "acl:relcl", "nsubj", "xcomp", "nsubj", "nmod", "case", "det", "amod"], "As a result, there are a number of things that make Globish different from the \"standard\" English."], [["nsubj", "nmod", "case", "appos", "compound", "nmod", "case", "det", "amod", "nmod", "case", "compound", "amod", "nummod", "amod"], "First of all, Globish vocabulary starts with a limited number of English words-just 1,500 easy words."], [["advmod", "nsubj", "dobj", "det", "amod", "amod"], "Also, Globish takes all different English spellings."], [["nmod", "case", "nsubj", "aux", "dobj", "cc:preconj", "cc", "conj"], "For example, people can use both theatre and theater."], [["advmod", "advmod", "advcl", "advmod", "nsubj", "dobj", "nsubj", "amod", "cop", "nmod:poss", "amod"], "Most importantly, when people use Globish, clear communication is their biggest concern."], [["nsubj", "det", "aux", "ccomp", "nsubj", "det", "dobj", "amod", "cc", "conj"], "Every speaker should help the listener understand his or her message."], [["advmod", "nsubj", "det", "compound", "aux", "xcomp", "mark", "dobj", "amod", "cc", "conj", "dobj", "compound"], "Therefore, a Globish speaker will try to use shorter sentences and keep grammar simple."], [["nmod", "case", "nsubj", "compound", "aux", "dobj", "det", "amod", "advmod", "cc", "conj", "dobj", "compound", "advcl", "mark", "ccomp", "nsubj", "det"], "In addition, Globish speakers may repeat the same sentences twice or add body language to help the listener understand."], [["nsubj", "aux", "neg", "dobj", "amod", "advcl", "mark", "nsubj", "aux", "neg", "dobj"], "They would not use such questions as \"You don't like cats?\""], [["case", "nmod:poss", "acl:relcl", "mark", "nsubj", "det", "aux", "neg", "ccomp", "advmod", "mark", "dobj", "det"], "in their talk because the listener may not know how to answer the question."], [["csubj", "mark", "ccomp", "nsubj", "det", "parataxis", "nsubj", "compound", "aux", "dobj", "nmod", "case"], "To help the listener understand, Globish speakers will ask \"Do you like cats?\""], [["advmod", "nsubj", "det", "aux", "dobj", "det", "nmod", "case", "det", "amod", "advcl", "mark", "discourse", "nsubj", "dobj"], "Then, the listener will answer the question with a full sentence like \"Yes, I like cats.\""], [["discourse", "discourse", "nsubj", "aux", "neg", "dobj"], "Or \"No, I don't like cats.\""], [["nsubj", "det", "nmod", "case", "xcomp", "nsubj", "nmod", "case", "det", "amod"], "A lot of people find Globish easier than the \"standard\" English."], [["advmod", "nsubj", "det", "ccomp", "nsubj", "aux", "cop", "advmod", "cc", "conj"], "However, some people think Globish can be too simple and direct."], [["nsubj", "aux", "xcomp", "cc", "conj", "advmod", "advcl", "advmod", "nsubj", "dobj", "amod", "advmod", "advmod", "cc", "conj"], "Speakers may become impolite or even rude when they use too much short and direct language."], [["nmod", "case", "det", "nsubj", "det", "nmod", "case", "det", "amod", "cc", "conj", "nmod:poss", "cop", "advmod", "cc", "conj", "aux", "cop"], "For some people, the study of the English language and its culture is still useful and can be fun."], [["advmod", "nsubj", "cop", "neg", "det", "amod", "nmod", "case", "det", "amod", "nmod", "case", "acl", "mark", "nmod", "case", "det", "amod"], "Yet, Globish is not an official language but a linguistic tool for people to use in this globalized world."], [["nsubj", "cop", "nmod", "case", "det", "amod", "nmod", "case", "amod", "amod", "nmod", "case", "det"], "It is one of the modern choices for busy working people around the world."]]